name: Trail Canyon Prospect
description:
Introduction

This unnamed canyon is a small tributary to Trail Canyon.

Approach

Follow 3N29 to the drop in.

Descent

  • R1: 100 ft, tree center
  • Moderate downclimb immediately prior to R2
  • R2: 60 ft, bush DCL
  • R3: 100 ft, bush DCR
  • Bushwhacking section
  • Alternate exit (trail crossing)
  • From the trail crossing to the creek is nontechnical

Exit

Optionally, hike an additional 0.65 miles and 250 ft elevation gain to Trail Canyon Falls and then turn around and follow the trail back downstream.

Follow the trail back to your vehicle.
